Klawitter, David   | Engineering Alumni | University of Illinois at Chicago                     It all starts with a single spark         Skip to the content of this page ,  the main menu , the site search form , the site home page .        UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni     Search the site     Toggle Menu      Search                  UIC Logo          Engineering Alumni      Engineering Alumni   Main Menu    News    Expand News menu           Dean's List    RISE Magazine         Events    Expand Events menu           Upcoming Events         Get Involved    Expand Get Involved menu           Join us on LinkedIn    Become a Mentor    Volunteer    Engineer your own involvement    Honor a Professor         Awards    Expand Awards menu           2019 Alumni Award Honorees    2018 Alumni Award Honorees    2017 Alumni Award Honorees         Give    Contact     Eyebrow menu    College of Engineering    Engineering Career Center    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map       Search                           David   Klawitter  President Elect                 About   A graduate from UIC in 2015, David Klawitter completed his BS in Civil Engineering. He joined the EAA that year as a board Member-at-Large, wanting to give back to the University that had been such an essential part of his education and development. David served an interim position as VP of Membership and developed the Ambassador Program as the Chair of the Student Engagement Committee.  David is now serving the UIC EAA as President Elect and continuing to grow the Ambassador program.  David is currently employed by Mackie Consultants in Rosemont, Illinois focusing on water resources engineering and site development.  He has a strong passion for engineering, leadership, the environment, and sustainability. David held the office of President for EcoCampus, UIC’s sustainability student organization.  He completed a number of Sustainability Fee Projects around the Chicago campus and was a part of an UIC team that won first place in the national USEPA 2014 RainWorks Challenge for Green Infrastructure.  He continues his passion for engineering and sustainability as a Research Affiliate with the UIC CME Department, working on residential water consumption modeling.  David is eager to share his engineering passion with students and confer with his fellow alumni.  David’s free time is filled with recreational running, ice-skating, golfing, and playing board games with friends.  He enjoys volunteering and community service opportunities. David is excited to see the EAA growing and wants to continue building relationships between alumni, the University, and its students.                    UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni       Contact   851 S. Morgan - SEO Rm. 811  Phone: 3129969422  MWilli60@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 